properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 10 at 4:27AM MST until January 10 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...Potential for Strong Winds Return to the Wind Prone Areas of
Southeast Wyoming Late Tonight Through Saturday Afternoon...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a Dense Fog
Advisory, which is in effect until 8 AM MST this morning.

* TIMING...Through 8 AM This Morning.

* VISIBILITY...Very low visibility of one quarter mile or less at
time.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Hazardous travel conditions
along Interstate 80 from Pine Bluffs to Sidney and Highways 385
and 26 in the southern Nebraska Panhandle.
properties.instruction:
A Dense Fog Advisory means visibilities will frequently be
reduced to less than one quarter mile. If driving...slow down...
use your headlights...and leave plenty of distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST THIS MORNING
